abstract: Canada immigration Min John McCallum says government will probably miss goal of admitting 10,000 Syrian refugees by end of year.
lead_paragraph: At least 10,000 Syrian refugees will be “certified” as permanent residents of Canada by year’s end but may not reach Canadian soil by then, the immigration minister said.

headline.main: Canada May Miss Goal to Admit 10,000 Refugees by Year’s End
headline.print_headline: The Americas; Canada: Pace Slows for Refugee Arrivals
